r%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EBureau of Administration%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EBureau of Economic Development%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EBureau of Finance%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EBureau of Human Resources%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EBureau of Technology%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EFacilities%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=left%3EOffice of the President%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EJob Summary%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%3C/P%3E%0A%3CDIV%3EUnder general supervision of management of the Bureau of Technology, responsible for advanced troubleshooting of PC/office equipment, repair work, equipment deployment, application/OS support and staff training.%26nbsp; Assists with leading and facilitating structure across all levels of the organization to deliver valued outcomes to drive business decisions. %26nbsp;%26nbsp;Analyzes user needs and software requirements to determine feasibility of design within time and constraints.%26nbsp; Ensures all system interfaces are operational for consistent reliable data transfer between multi-tiered platforms.%26nbsp; Develops and directs software system testing and validation procedures, programing and documentation.%26nbsp; Assumes primary responsibility for multiple projects as directed.%26nbsp; Performs other related assignments and duties as directed.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CB%3E%26nbsp;%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=left%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3ETypical Duties%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3EAnalyzes user needs and software requirements to determine feasibility of design within time and constraints.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3EDevelops and directs software system testing and validation procedures, programing and documentation while conducting on-site diagnosis and repair of Personal Computers (PCs), laptops, monitors and peripherals.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3ESupervises projects to identify, analyze, and order replacement parts as needed.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3ETrains staff to diagnose, troubleshoot and support all information software in the County as needed.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3EParticipates in team meetings and project meetings and provides Tier 1 phone support as needed.%3C/DIV%3E','!*!%3CDIV align=left%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EMinimum Qualifications%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CUL%3E%0A%3CLI%3EGraduation from an accredited college or university with an Associate’s Degree %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E.%26nbsp; %3CSTRONG%3E(Must provide original college/university transcript at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E %0A%3CLI%3E%3CSTRONG%3EFour (4)%3C/STRONG%3E years of work experience as a Field Technician SUPPLEMENTED WITH a current CompTIA A+ certification; %3CB%3EOR%3C/B%3E Six (6) years of work experience as a Computer Field Technician %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. (%3CSTRONG%3EIf applicable, must provide proof of certification at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E %0A%3CLI%3EExperience with Microsoft Office Suite and Windows 7 platform %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %0A%3CLI%3EExperience with computer technology, installation and configuration of workstation equipment %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %0A%3CLI%3EExperience with networking essentials and wireless connectivity %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %0A%3CLI%3EValid driver’s license and proof of automobile insurance %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %3CSTRONG%3E(Must provide license and proof of insurance at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E %0A%3CLI%3E%3CSTRONG%3EMust be able%3C/STRONG%3E to work on-call 24/7 including weekends and holidays as assigned.%26nbsp;%3C/LI%3E%3C/UL%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EKnowledge, Skills, Abilities and Other Characteristics%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3EThorough knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite and Windows 7 platform including familiarity with Apple iOS and Android.%26nbsp;Thorough knowledge of computer technology, installation and configuration of workstation equipment.%26nbsp;Thorough knowledge of networking essentials and wireless connectivity.%26nbsp;Skilled in problem-solving with strong attention to detail.%26nbsp;Excellent customer service skills and the ability to react diplomatically and patiently to internal and external customers. Excellent follow-up skills paired with the ability to multi-task and determine root causes.%26nbsp;Strong written and verbal communication skills coupled with the ability to read, analyze and interpret technical procedures.%26nbsp;Strong response time to phone calls, emails and customer requests.%26nbsp;Adhere to department policies and standards.%26nbsp;Ability to prioritize, plan, and organize tasks based upon user requirements.%26nbsp;Ability to manage multiple projects utilizing best practices based on departmental priorities.%26nbsp;Ability to work independently under minimal supervision in stressful situations and meet deadlines.%26nbsp;This position occasionally requires various types of physical exertion including but not limited to climbing, lifting, pulling, pushing, and moving moderate to heavy weight.%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3E%3CB%3EThe duties listed are not set forth for purposes of limiting the assignment of work.%26nbsp; They are not to be construed as a complete list of the many duties normally to be performed under a job title or those to be performed temporarily outside an employee%27s normal line of work.%3C/B%3E%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3E%3CSTRONG%3E%3C/STRONG%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CSTRONG%3ECOOK COUNTY GOVERNMENT IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/P%3E','Repost','00114764','false','78140','78140','true','78140','false','Submission for the position: FIELD TECHNICIAN II-BUREAU OF TECHNOLOGY - (Job Number: 00114933)','false','78140','false','true','https://cookcountyil.taleo.net/careersection/jobdetail.ftl?job=78140%26lang=en','FIELD TECHNICIAN II-BUREAU OF TECHNOLOGY','true']);
