eau of Economic Development%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Finance%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Human Resources%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Technology%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EFacilities%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EOffice of the President%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%3C/STRONG%3E%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp; %3C/DIV%3E%3C/BLOCKQUOTE%3E%3C/TD%3E%3C/TR%3E%3C/TBODY%3E%3C/TABLE%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EJOB SUMMARY%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EUnder the general direction of the Contract Compliance Director, provides administrative support to assist the departmental staff in matters regarding Minority, Women, and/or Veteran owned Business Enterprises (M/W/VBE).%26nbsp; Reviews and verifies all submitted certification applications, documents and supporting documentation to ensure they meet M/WBE Program guidelines.%26nbsp; Conducts initial review of bid, proposal, and/or contract submittals for compliance to the M/WBE Program and assists with filing, coding, information processing, assisting clients and visitors, and noting record discrepancies; as well as assists in outreach efforts.%26nbsp; Prepares correspondence; schedules tentative appointments; arranges conferences and meetings; and assembles established background materials as directed. Verifies M/WBE certifications from the County of Cook and/or the City of Chicago, and monitors the directory of Certified M/WBEs maintained by Cook County.%26nbsp; May perform other duties as assigned.%3C/DIV%3E','!*!%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CSTRONG%3E%3CU%3EMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS%3C/U%3E%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/P%3E%0A%3CUL%3E%0A%3CLI%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EPossession of a High School diploma or General Education Development (GED) certificate %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. (Must provide proof at time of interview)%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CLI%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CSTRONG%3EThree (3)%3C/STRONG%3E years of full-time administrative work in procurement, contract compliance, equal employment opportunity or a supplier diversity program; %3CB%3EOR%3C/B%3E Graduation from an accredited college or university with an Associate’s Degree SUPPLEMENTED WITH %3CSTRONG%3Eone (1)%3C/STRONG%3E year full-time administrative work experience in procurement, contract compliance, equal employment opportunity or a supplier diversity program %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %3CSTRONG%3E(If applicable, must provide original college/university transcript at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CLI%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EPossession of a current valid driver’s license %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %3CSTRONG%3E(Must provide license at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%3C/LI%3E%3C/UL%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22 align=justify%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EKNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, ABILITIES AND OTHER CHARACTERISTICS%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%3CB%3E%26nbsp;%3C/B%3E%3C/P%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CB%3E%3C/B%3E%0A%3CDIV%3EKnowledge of the principles/techniques of bidding practices and procedures ensuring the utilization of and payment to MBE/WBE vendors. Skill in the use of Microsoft Word, Excel, Power Point and Access. Skill in planning and developing complex assignments with minimal direction. Ability to work independently in composing memoranda/reports. Ability to meet project deadlines. Ability to gather information from vendors and make inquiries determining whether contract bidders follow the MBE/WBE guidelines. Ability to gather information from vendors and make inquiries pertaining to their certification. Ability to convey information and explain or describe basic office policy and procedure to others. Excellent communication skills with the ability to prepare written reports and presentations.%26nbsp;Interpersonal skills to work with a wide variety of people with varying levels of experience. This position occasionally requires moderate to extensive travel to work assignment throughout Cook County for which the employee must provide his or her own means of transportation.%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CB%3EThe duties listed are not set forth for purposes of limiting the assignment of work.%26nbsp; They are not to be construed as a complete list of the many duties normally to be performed under a job title or those to be performed temporarily outside an employee%27s normal line of work.%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CSTRONG%3ECOOK COUNTY IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/P%3E','','','false','78020','78020','true','78020','false','Submission for the position: ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT II CONTRACT COMPLIANCE - (Job Number: 00114929)','false','78020','false','true','https://cookcountyil.taleo.net/careersection/jobdetail.ftl?job=78020%26lang=en','ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT II CONTRACT COMPLIANCE','true']);
