%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Finance%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Human Resources%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EBureau of Technology%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EFacilities%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV%3E%3CSTRONG%3EOffice of the President%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%3C/STRONG%3E%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%26nbsp; %3C/DIV%3E%3C/BLOCKQUOTE%3E%3C/TD%3E%3C/TR%3E%3C/TBODY%3E%3C/TABLE%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CSTRONG%3E%3CU%3EJOB SUMMARY%3C/U%3E%3C/STRONG%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EFunctions as an Accounting Financial Analyst under the general direction of the Director of Financial Reporting and Director of Financial Control IV in the General Accounting Department (GAD) of the office.%26nbsp; Directs the supervision of the County’s books and records of accounts reflecting receipts, disbursements, assets, liabilities and financial position. Directs compilation of data and preparation of financial/operating reports for planning effective administration of County activities by management.%26nbsp; Works in tandem with the County’s leadership to assist in the annual external audit process to the GAD. Assists with general obligation bond sales relating to the preparation of official written statements and coordinates with various county department officials, attorneys and bond underwriters to ensure accuracy in the above mentioned bond sales.%26nbsp; Submits work for final review and approval to the Director of Financial Reporting/Director of Financial Control IV. Performs other duties as assigned.%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E','!*!%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CDIV align=left%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS%3C/U%3E%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CUL%3E%0A%3CLI%3EGraduation from an accredited college or university with a Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting, Finance or Business Administration%26nbsp;%3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E.%26nbsp; (%3CSTRONG%3EMust provide original college/university transcript at time of interview)%3C/STRONG%3E%3CSTRONG%3EFive (5)%3C/STRONG%3E years’ full-time work experience in an Analyst, Auditor or Accountant position %3CSTRONG%3Eis required.%3C/STRONG%3E %0A%3CLI%3EExperience utilizing Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Systems %3CSTRONG%3Eis required%3C/STRONG%3E. %0A%3CLI%3EA Master’s Degree in Accounting, Finance or Business Administration%3CSTRONG%3E may be preferred.%3C/STRONG%3E %0A%3CLI%3ECertified Public Accountant (CPA) %3CSTRONG%3Eis preferred.%3C/STRONG%3E%26nbsp;%3C/LI%3E%3C/UL%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CB%3E%3CU%3EKNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, ABILITIES AND OTHER CHARACTERISTICS%3C/U%3E%26nbsp;%3C/B%3E%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EGeneral knowledge of professional accounting standards and pronouncements.%26nbsp;%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3EAbility to produce/review financial reports.%26nbsp;Skill in supervising books and records of accounts, disbursements, assets and liabilities.%26nbsp;General knowledge of financial/accounting analysis relating to various bonds and revenues.%26nbsp;General knowledge of the financial setting of County government or other governmental agencies as they relate to various revenues and bonds.%26nbsp;Skill in ERP Systems, Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook, Access and VISIO.%26nbsp;Skill in overseeing cash receipts and disbursement reports through general ledger trial balances and bank statements.%26nbsp;Excellent oral and written communication skills.%26nbsp;Ability to produce and review financial reports.%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CDIV align=justify%3E%3CB%3EThe duties listed are not set forth for purposes of limiting the assignment of work.%26nbsp; They are not to be construed as a complete list of the many duties normally to be performed under a job title or those to be performed temporarily outside an employee%27s normal line of work.%3C/B%3E%26nbsp;%3C/DIV%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%26nbsp;%3C/P%3E%0A%3CP style=%22MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px%22%3E%3CSTRONG%3ECOOK COUNTY IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER%3C/STRONG%3E%3C/P%3E','','','false','77920','77920','true','77920','false','Submission for the position: DIRECTOR OF FINANCIAL CONTROL II-COMPTROLLER - (Job Number: 00114923)','false','77920','false','true','https://cookcountyil.taleo.net/careersection/jobdetail.ftl?job=77920%26lang=en','DIRECTOR OF FINANCIAL CONTROL II-COMPTROLLER','true']);
